> If you've been on the request line for light, tasty, satisfying and vegan dinner ideas, this one's going out to you. First you'll smash chickpeas (to create jagged edges for browning) and roast with sweet potato, cumin, and curry until crispy, then add to sauteed peas, onion, garlic, ginger, with a bright squeeze of lemon. Stuff all that warm goodness into crisp, cool lettuce leaves, drizzle with a tangy red pepper-cilantro sauce and it's vegan wrap music for your taste buds.

== Roasted Chickpeas & Sweet Potato ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @sweet potatoes{1} into ¼-inch pieces.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%400g can}; thoroughly pat dry with #paper towels{}. On a clean flat work surface, place chickpeas between 2 large pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Smash with a #mortar{} or the bottom of a pan until broken apart (chickpeas should not be completely mashed).

In a #large bowl{}, combine sweet potato, smashed chickpeas, half the @cumin{1%tsp} (all for 4 servings), 1 tsp @curry powder{1%tbsp} (2 tsp for 4), a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; toss until evenly coated. Spread out on a #baking sheet{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. (For 4, divide everything between 2 sheets; roast on top and middle racks, swapping positions halfway through.)

== Filling ==

While veggies roast, halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Halve @lemon{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and a pinch of salt; cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and softened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium and add @peas{4%oz}. Cook, stirring occasionally until browned, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

Add garlic and ginger to pan; cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, ~{1-3%minutes}.

Stir in remaining @curry powder{}, ½ cup water (1 cup for 4 servings), ¼ tsp salt (½ tsp for 4), and juice from half the lemon. Cook, stirring occasionally, until water has mostly evaporated, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

Stir roasted chickpea mixture into pan. Taste and season filling with salt and pepper if desired.

== Red Pepper Cilantro Sauce ==

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @red pepper jam{2}, @cilantro{}, 1 TBSP water (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and juice from remaining lemon. Cover tightly with plastic wrap and microwave until warmed through, ~{20-30%seconds}.

== Assembly ==

Divide lettuce leaves between plates (pat dry if needed). Fill leaves with chickpea filling. Drizzle with as much sauce as you like and serve.